The paper deals with algorithms for selection and sorting of numbers, which are fundamental problems in computer science and fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of adversarial comparators and the analysis of algorithms against non-adaptive and adaptive adversaries suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The application of the algorithms to density estimation indicates a connection to machine learning and statistics, which are covered by the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
